To connect your **Vegelo** app to a Google Sheets backend via Google Apps Script, I will implement a robust data-fetching layer in the frontend and provide you with the exact script to deploy.

### Specification
1.  **Google Apps Script Integration**:
    *   The app will now fetch the product catalog directly from a Google Sheet on startup.
    *   The Admin panel's "Add" and "Edit" functions will send real-time `POST` requests to the Apps Script to update the Sheet.
    *   Changes made by the admin are instantly persistent for all users globally.
2.  **Admin UI Enhancements**:
    *   Added a "Syncing" indicator so you know when the database is updating.
    *   Optimistic UI updates: The app will update locally immediately while the background sync completes.
3.  **Visual Polish**:
    *   Maintains the premium "Vegelo" branding.
    *   The hidden 5-tap gesture on the logo remains the only way to reveal the Admin entry point.
4.  **Google Apps Script (GAS) Code**:
    *   I've provided the script below. You will need to paste this into a new Google Apps Script project attached to a Google Sheet.

### 1. The Google Apps Script (Deployment Instructions)
Create a new Google Sheet, go to **Extensions > Apps Script**, and paste this code. **Deploy as a Web App** with access set to "Anyone".

```javascript
// Google Apps Script for Vegelo Backend
const SHEET_NAME = "Products";

function setup() {
  const ss = SpreadsheetApp.getActiveSpreadsheet();
  let sheet = ss.getSheetByName(SHEET_NAME);
  if (!sheet) {
    sheet = ss.insertSheet(SHEET_NAME);
    sheet.appendRow(["id", "name", "price", "image", "category", "unit", "description"]);
  }
}

function doGet() {
  const sheet = SpreadsheetApp.getActiveSpreadsheet().getSheetByName(SHEET_NAME);
  const data = sheet.getDataRange().getValues();
  const headers = data.shift();
  const products = data.map(row => {
    const obj = {};
    headers.forEach((header, i) => obj[header] = row[i]);
    return obj;
  });

  return ContentService.createTextOutput(JSON.stringify(products))
    .setMimeType(ContentService.MimeType.JSON);
}

function doPost(e) {
  const params = JSON.parse(e.postData.contents);
  const ss = SpreadsheetApp.getActiveSpreadsheet();
  const sheet = ss.getSheetByName(SHEET_NAME);
  const data = sheet.getDataRange().getValues();

  if (params.action === 'add' || params.action === 'edit') {
    const p = params.product;
    const rowData = [p.id, p.name, p.price, p.image, p.category, p.unit, p.description];

    let foundIndex = -1;
    for (let i = 1; i < data.length; i++) {
      if (data[i][0] == p.id) {
        foundIndex = i + 1;
        break;
      }
    }

    if (foundIndex > -1) {
      sheet.getRange(foundIndex, 1, 1, rowData.length).setValues([rowData]);
    } else {
      sheet.appendRow(rowData);
    }
  } else if (params.action === 'delete') {
    for (let i = 1; i < data.length; i++) {
      if (data[i][0] == params.id) {
        sheet.deleteRow(i + 1);
        break;
      }
    }
  }

  return ContentService.createTextOutput(JSON.stringify({status: 'success'}))
    .setMimeType(ContentService.MimeType.JSON);
}
```

